        Keeping .fastq: grep -B1 -A2 NNNNNNNNNN SRR098026.fastq (searches all lines for 10+ 'N's in the file while preserving fastq files)

        'bad-reads.fastq': grep -B1 -A2 NNNNNNNNNN SRR098026.fastq > bad-reads.fastq (WHEN MAKING .fastq WE WANT THE SAME FORMAT AS .fastq SO NEED THE FOUR LINES SO -B1 and -A2 ARE NECESSARY FOR THIS TASK!)
            -v = inverse command --> removes desired sequence
            -B1 = 1 line before line with search
            -A2 = 2 lines after line with search
            '^--' means only at the beginning of the line, search for these dashes
            -h removes the header
            --no-group-separator removes the separator (typically denoted as -- by default)

